gmx:name.gco:CharacterString: Feature catalog for United States National Transportation Atlas Railroads, 1998-2002

gfc:definition.gco:CharacterString: The lines represent a comprehensive database of the nation's railway system at 1:100,000 scale. The data set covers the 48 contiguous States plus the District of Columbia within United States.
The unique sequential identification for the railroad feature in the network structure.
The name or identification for the railroad feature.

The reporting mark of the first owning railroad feature. A mark of 'XXXX' indicates an abandoned railroad feature. Rule 260 codes are used where available. A mark of 'DUMX' indicates an added connecting railroad feature.
Reporting mark of the first railroad feature having trackage-rights.
The type of passenger railroad feature indicator.
Rail line now used for rapid transit.
The type of military interest railroad feature indicator - this code should match the publication 'Civil Rail Lines Important to National Defense, December 1998'.
A connector to the Strategic Rail Corridor Network (STRACNET) system.
On the Strategic Rail Corridor Network (STRACNET) system.
The Federal Railroad Administration (FRA) region number for the railroad feature.
The measure of distance in miles.
